The `ignore` in `content.json` should be set to `"(data/.*db|data/users/.*|node_modules/.*|src/.*|.vscode|.git|disabled/.*|package-lock.json)"`

ok, I don't want to change that right now, but I somewhat agree on you..

If you could use the inspector to change the css properties of `#sidebar-left.app-sidebar.off-canvas-sidebar` to the following (just untick the properties in the style-view):

```
@media (min-width: 960px)
.off-canvas .off-canvas-sidebar {
    /* -webkit-box-flex: 0; */
    -ms-flex: 0 0 auto;
    /* flex: 0 0 auto; */
    /* position: relative; */
    /* -webkit-transform: none; */
    /* transform: none; */
}
```

And then toggling `transform: none` on and off would maybe achieve the wanted behavior?

I could also just add another option to toggle that stuff, because I for my part would like to see all conversations at one peek.

@krixano, how exactly did you implement the search in other zites?
Did you use CORS, or the merger feature?

Because I thought I could maybe just fetch all the data from the current thunderwave with one of those methods, to show it in the beta, but I'm not sure on how I would do it, so that I can use normal dbQueries :thinking:

